OL,3,C'People assume I'm on drugs' - man
OL,4,Cwith cerebral palsy on discrimination
OL,6,FHe says he wanted to speak out to help
OL,7,Fprevent younger people with the
OL,8,Fcondition from experiencing the
OL,9,Fcomments he has had to face.
OL,11,F"I've been accused of being drunk at
OL,12,F9am cycling through Bristol to go to a
OL,13,Fmeeting," he said.
