OL,3,C'People assume I'm on drugs' - man
OL,4,Cwith cerebral palsy on discrimination
OL,6,F"People just assume that I've had
OL,7,Falcohol or ketamine. Because someone
OL,8,Fdoes an illegal drug gets that way
OL,9,Ftherefore I'm not allowed, when I
OL,10,Fcan't help it, to do stuff. That's
OL,11,Fwrong. They'll wake up and they'll be
OL,12,Fbetter - I'll wake up and I won't be
OL,13,Fany better.
OL,15,F"I'm different and that worries people
OL,16,Fbut I'm not different because I'm
OL,17,Funique, I'm different because I have a
OL,18,Fdisability."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
