OL,3,C'People assume I'm on drugs' - man
OL,4,Cwith cerebral palsy on discrimination
OL,6,F"We were supposed to be seen and not
OL,7,Fheard - just put in the corner. It's
OL,8,Fchanged loads."
OL,10,FDespite the continual challenges Nik
OL,11,Ffaces, he says he will not give up,
OL,12,Fsaying: "My doctors have told me in
OL,13,Fthe past I've got every right to lay
OL,14,Fdown and let the carers do it for me.
OL,16,F"No man, I do that and that's giving
OL,17,Fin to CP and I won't give in to it."
